    <body>
        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Note: &lt;/b&gt;">If your SQL instance does not appear in the SQL Server field, you may need to turn on the SQL Server Browser or manually type in the computer name/SQL Server instance name. To turn on the SQL Server Browser, do this: (1) Open the SQL Configuration manager; (2) select <span class="Emphasis">SQL Server Services</span> in the left pane; (3) right-click <span class="Emphasis">SQL server browser</span> and select <span class="Emphasis">Properties</span>; (4) on the <span class="Emphasis">Service</span> tab, select start mode to <span class="Emphasis">Automatic</span> and click <span class="Emphasis">OK</span>; (5) right-click the <span class="Emphasis">SQL Server Browser</span> again, and select <span class="Emphasis">Start</span>.</p>
    </body>
